    "description": "This PR adds a `supp_data_dir` config option for a location to store supplemental data tables (like those used by `add_xray_emissivity_field`), and a new command-line option, `yt download`, to download files from http://yt-project.org/data. The latter allows downloading to `test_data_dir`, `supp_data_dir`, or any other location.\r\n\r\nExample executions:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ yt download apec_emissivity_v2.h5 supp_data_dir\r\n```\r\n```bash\r\n$ yt download GasSloshing.tar.gz test_data_dir\r\n```\r\n```bash\r\n$ yt download ZeldovichPancake.tar.gz /Users/jzuhone/workspace\r\n```\r\n\r\nI need some help figuring out how to get the bulleted list in the `description` field to be rendered with the link breaks--anything I try doesn't seem to work.\r\n\r\n",
